column60: Built by a builder for his own family, this brick and stone classic Tudor has over 1,600 sq. ft. Set on a deep lot just steps away from Garfield Park, there is a 3-car garage and a 4th bay for storage. Spacious living room with a stone fireplace and gas insert. The formal dining room has leaded glass China cabinets and a door leading to the back covered porch. The kitchen has a dinette. The main level also has a 1/2 bath and vestibule. The second level offers a large master with deep closet area; the 2nd bedroom has a walk-in closet and access to an upper porch and the 3rd bedroom has extra wide front windows. The main upper bath has linen space, plus there is an additional linen closet and coat closet in the upper hall. There is also a cedar closet between the 1st & 2nd levels. The 4th bedroom on the 3rd floor is 26X15. Hardwood flooring under all carpeted areas. Glass block windows in bsmt.

column60: This 2-bedroom, 1-bath ranch in Garfield Heights welcomes you with a recently painted aluminum siding exterior (2024), a front porch, and a single-car garage with opener! Step inside to a bright living room featuring hardwood floors, flowing into the dining area and functional kitchen—perfect for everyday living or entertaining! Down the hall, you’ll find two bedrooms and a full bathroom, all thoughtfully maintained and move-in ready! The home features a new H2O tank (2024), sump pump (2022), furnace (2016), newer windows, and an updated electrical panel! The full basement provides ample storage or potential additional living space, making this home as practical as it is comfortable! Enjoy a private backyard, recently painted aluminum siding (2024), a single-car garage with opener, newer garage and side doors, roof with gutter guards (2017), retaining wall (2005), and front porch with added insulation (2005)! With all major systems addressed, this home is in very good condition, ideal for investors or first-time homebuyers! Located within walking distance to Marymount Hospital and just minutes from Garfield Park Reservation, the Garfield Heights Civic Center, and Turney Town Shopping Center, plus quick highway access to downtown Cleveland! Buyer to assume POS! Full service property management is available with dedicated departments for leasing, marketing, and tenant communication! Plus, rehab and construction services are offered for remote investors, making this property a turnkey opportunity for rental income or long-term investment! Don't miss out on this solid opportunity! Schedule a showing to see it for yourself!

column60: Cape Cod with 3 (possibly 4) Bedrooms and 2-1/2 Baths * Located on a large (almost) 1/2 acre lot on a quiet secluded street * This home is very unique as the owner created many customized features in the home * On the first floor you'll find a spacious and cozy Family Room with a decorative fireplace and hardwood floors *  Eat in Kitchen with built in appliances and cute built ins in the nook area * A huge Dining Room space with hardwood floors * An office/bedroom that has a sink and plumbing for a toilet (previously used as a bedroom/bathroom for an elderly person), now has a built in desk in it to be used for an office (this room has baseboard heat) * Off the back of the house you'll find a mudroom area with a freezer and a Full Bathroom off the Kitchen that has washer/dryer hookups and a walk in shower * On the second floor you'll find another Full Bathroom off the hallway and 3/4 Bedrooms * A few Bedrooms are regular Bedrooms, however, the others are quite different with another Bedroom off of the one with a built in bed set up and the one towards the back of the home has another room off of it (could be a play room, sitting room etc.) *  The Basement has glass block windows, updated electrical boxes, sump pump and a newer HWT (2011) * The roof (complete tear off) was done in the last 9-10 years * In the back of the wooded/treed yard you can find pear trees and raspberry and blackberry bushes * This home is located in a great area, close to Garfield Metro Parks and Tinkers Creek * Seller will make no repairs and Buyers to assume POS violations * With a little updating and TLC this home can become a house again !

column60: Welcome home to this inviting 3-bedroom, 1-bathroom ranch-style residence that perfectly blends comfort and convenience. Step inside to discover beautiful natural wooden floors that bring warmth and character to the living spaces. The open floor plan offers seamless flow between the cozy living room and the well-equipped kitchen and a dining room, which comes complete with a refrigerator and washer & dryer included—making move-in a breeze. Each of the three bedrooms provides ample natural light and space for relaxation or work-from-home needs. The full bathroom is newly updated, ready for your personal touch. Outside, enjoy your own private backyard oasis—perfect for entertaining, gardening, or simply unwinding in peace. The attached garage offers secure parking and additional storage. Ideal for first-time buyers, downsizers, or anyone seeking a low-maintenance lifestyle, this home offers both comfort and functionality in a classic ranch-style layout. Don’t miss this opportunity to make it yours!

column60:
Located in Garfield Heights, this 3-bedroom, 1-bath home offers a balance of space, comfort, and location. The first
floor includes a welcoming living room, two bedrooms, and an eat-in kitchen, while the upper level provides an
additional bedroom or multipurpose area. A detached garage and a spacious yard complete the property, with
convenient access to schools, parks, and major roadways.

column60: Plymouth Rock? More like Plymouth ROCKS!! Yes, this beautifully UPDATED bungalow on Plymouth Avenue boasts three marvelous bedrooms, one spectacular bathroom, and a host of other fetching features! The house is currently tenanted on a MTM lease at $1350 a month, so it's an amazing investor's dream!! Beyond the cash flow, just look at that dynamic flooring underfoot...so luxurious and oh-so lovely. Once you make your way to the spacious, open kitchen, you'll see how appetizing the captivating cabinetry and new appliances are. Mmm. Delicious. The remodeled bathroom is sure to please, as are the beautiful bedrooms. Add in a giant basement, a quaint porch out back, a detached garage, and a massive back yard, and there's only one thing left to ask: When are you coming "home"?

column60: Welcome to this charming 3-bedroom, 1.5-bath townhome nestled in the heart of Garfield Heights! This well-maintained home offers a perfect blend of comfort and convenience, ideal for first-time buyers, downsizers, or investors. Step into a spacious living room filled with natural light, leading to a cozy dining area with sliding glass doors that open onto the backyard—perfect for seamless indoor-outdoor living. The functional kitchen offers ample cabinet space, and the main level features a convenient half bath for guests. Upstairs, you'll find three generously sized bedrooms and a full bath. The full-size basement features laundry hookups and offers ample potential for storage, a home gym, or future finishing. Located near schools, shopping, parks, and with easy access to I-480 and I-77, this home combines comfort with commuter-friendly living.

column60: This tenant occupied cape cod is a great way to bring a cash-flowing single family into your portfolio! With a long-term tenant (3+ years) in place, the property rents for $1,272/month. The lease is through 6/30/25 and the tenant would like to sign an extension. Professional property management is available, full service including rehab/rent-ready project management! Solid low maintenance features include vinyl siding, vinyl windows, 3-tab roof, younger HVAC, younger electrical panel and hardwood floors throughout first floor and carpeting on the 2nd! The home has 3 bedrooms, 2 on the main floor and 1 on the 2nd dormer floor and 1 full bath on the main floor. There is a full basement partially finished with rec room, front porch and detached 2-car garage. Located in an area of Garfield Heights with high rental demand, it's close to the Garfield Park Reservation, has easy highway and is close to schools, shopping, food and more! Full service property management available with dedicated departments for leasing, marketing, tenant communication. Plus rehab and construction services for remote investors!

Welcome to 10401 Grace Ave in Garfield Heights! Sitting on a spacious corner lot, this charming 2-bedroom home with a bonus room is almost completely renovated—just waiting on your finishing touches to make it your own!

You’ll love the fresh feel throughout thanks to new carpet, updated flooring, and recently upgraded major mechanicals. Whether you're a first-time buyer, downsizer, or investor looking for your next rental-ready property, this one checks all the boxes for comfort, value, and potential.

With a flexible bonus room perfect for a home office, playroom, or guest space, this home adapts to your lifestyle. The large lot offers room to garden, entertain, or simply relax.

Don’t wait—homes like this don’t last long. Schedule your showing today!

Currently rented on a month-to-month lease, making it a great opportunity for investors or owner-occupants. Monthly rent is $1,200. Being sold as-is.

column60:
Solid 2-Bedroom Brick Ranch – Investor Special or Perfect Starter Home

Opportunity knocks with this classic 2-bedroom, 1-bath brick ranch, full of potential and ready for your personal touch. Whether you're an investor looking for your next project or a homeowner eager to make a space your own, this property is the perfect canvas.

Featuring a functional layout with a spacious living area, eat-in kitchen, and two generously sized bedrooms, this home offers a solid foundation and great bones. The full basement adds valuable square footage and could easily be transformed into an entertainment space, home office, or even an additional bedroom.

Situated on a nice-sized lot in a quiet neighborhood, there's room to grow inside and out. With a little vision and some updates, this home could truly shine.

Don’t miss this value-packed opportunity—bring your ideas and unlock the potential!

column60:
Welcome home to this well-maintained 2-bedroom Cape Cod full of character. Featuring beautiful hardwood floors throughout, this inviting home offers a warm and comfortable living space. The updated bathroom provides a fresh and stylish touch, while a convenient additional bathroom is located in the basement.

Enjoy the bonus finished third floor—ideal for a home office, guest room, or creative space. The kitchen includes a stainless steel refrigerator, combining functionality with sleek style.

Property is being sold as is. Buyer to assume any Point of Sale (POS) violations. Don’t miss this opportunity to own a charming home with plenty of potential!

column60:
Attention investors or first-time buyers.
This adorable 3 bedroom, 1 bath home is waiting for you.
The tenant is paying $1300 per month, plus all utilities.
Tenant's lease goes month to month effective 8.31.25.
Home will be POS compliant by closing.
The foundation was re-done in 2019. New furnace 2022, hot water tank 2024, LVP flooring upstairs 2022, 
washing machine 2021, new fridge 2020, back steps replaced 2021.The home has vinyl windows.
24 hours' notice for showings.  Excellent central location. Minutes to downtown, the east or west sides. Close to restaurants, shopping, medical, educational facilities and highways.

column60:
Location, Location, Location! 

This single-family home is packed with potential. The exterior just needs a little touch-up. It is in a prime location, just minutes from Garfield Heights High School, Metroparks, and shopping. It features a private garage that offers secure parking and extra storage. Inside, you’ll find a stunning, oversized round archway with two built-in cabinets that beautifully separate the living and dining room, adding charm and character. Upstairs, a fully finished attic provides a flexible space for a master bedroom, guest suite, playroom, or a cozy retreat. 

Why rent when you can pay less and own your own home?

Schedule your appointment today!

column60: •Property is being sold in an "as is" condition, and the condition is unknown and may include defects, possible health or safety hazards, or debris, or be located in a Special Flood Hazard Area.     •Proof of Funds Required. The seller requires that the high bidder be able to demonstrate proof of funds or financing pre-qualification within 24 hours of the auction. Buyer must obtain a "pre-qualification" letter from a lender of their choice. If buyer intends to pay with cash, a bank letter or other financial account statement showing proof of sufficient funds to cover 100% of the purchase price will be required (account numbers should be removed or redacted). Buyer understands and agrees to submit said documentation to auctioneer within 24 hours of the auction.     •Utilities Disclosure. The utilities to this property are not currently "turned on" and the property has been winterized. Utilities will not be turned prior to closing, regardless of inspections. Buyer will need to consider this and account for it if/when inspecting the property. Buyer is responsible for utility transfer post-closing.  Buyer agrees to hold Seller, Williams & Williams, and its agents harmless from any and all results therein.  Buyer is advised to conduct a thorough investigation of the property's utility usage and any associated costs and expenses associated with usage.    •Buyer understands and acknowledges that square footage, acreage, and/or bedroom and bathroom count for the building sited on the property is based on an appraisal or county assessor information.  Buyer further understands and acknowledges that measurements/acreage/count can vary from a few feet to several hundred feet regardless of source (County Assessor's records, appraisal, or appraisal measurement report, etc.) and that said sources may contain erroneous information or measurements/acreage/count.     Buyer should conduct their own investigation and satisfy that the size and/or square footage, acreage, and bedroom/bathroom count of the dwelling/building is acceptable to the Buyer prior to placing any bid or offer on a property.      By placing a bid or offer on a property, Buyer is accepting the property in "as-is where-is condition" and agrees to be bound to the bid or offer should a discrepancy arise.

column60:
Prime Commercial Land Opportunity in Garfield Heights!

Don’t miss this rare opportunity to own a high-visibility commercial lot located directly in front of the bustling Giant Eagle Plaza on Vista Way in Garfield Heights, Ohio. This vacant parcel offers exceptional exposure with steady foot and vehicle traffic, making it an ideal location for retail, dining, office space, or a service-based business.

Surrounded by established national and local retailers, and just minutes from I-480, this lot provides convenient accessibility and endless potential for development in a thriving commercial corridor. Whether you’re a seasoned investor or a business owner ready to build, this location offers the visibility and traffic flow to help your business succeed.

Highlights:
 • Prime location in front of Giant Eagle Plaza
 • High traffic and visibility
 • Easy access to major highways
 • Perfect for new construction in a growing commercial area

Secure your spot in one of Garfield Heights’ most active retail hubs!
